p align=left class=m><span class=title> ....</span><hr size=1> 'Go to the Docks (Left side from zone entrance). On the second pier, there's an NPC for a quest concerning rats.<br><br>Two rats spawn on the beach area.<br><br>The quest rat spawns inside the &quot;warehouse&quot;.<br><br>Big Exp for turning in the tooth.'<br><br>Stormtower hit the nail on the head, at level 10 the teeth would be fantastic experience.  If you ask me though, do it this way, get the enchanter to level 13 or so, then team up and kill the rat in the house until you hit level 20 and the enchanter 17 or so.  He is a 10 minute spawn and at level 20 I could kill him and when I handed in the teeth, it gave me a blue bubble of experience (combining killing and tooth I meant).  The loot is horrible (as in non existent), but the experience is fantastic and the risk is 0 unless you kill too many cats. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/29/01 7:18:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=753.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ....</span><hr size=1> Simple Answer: Group Together Anyway.<br><br>Finding groups on this server is going to be difficult for many, and we have got to break outselves of the habit that a good group stays within a range of a few leves, at least until we hit level 40 or so.  So, group with him anyway, and make sure you hunt stuff that he can deal with, rather than taking on stuff that's good xp for you.  You may find you attract other characters of the Enchanter's level into groups, because having a tank of a level higher than the rest of the group can be a huge asset.<br><br>While it's true, as a higher level character, you will suck more than your fair share of the xp a lot of the time, the difference in what you need to level vs. what a level 10 needs to level will quickly become apparent.  If you always group with this enchanter, assuming he doesnt' die constantly, his level will catch up soon enough.<br><br>Right, that's my advise to everyone.  Instead of looking for the perfect group/partner to appear, be willing to cultivate it.  And I applaud the fact that you are trying to help a friend up, rather than just griping that there aren't any people to group with.  Unless you play significiantly longer hours that he does, he'll get there, no worries.<br><br>Valquiss Silverpalm<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vallya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/30/01 9:36:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=753.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ....</span><hr size=1> Get a bind in the pool room outside The Warrens. Then go in and refuse to turn tail and run when the trains come in. I &quot;managed&quot;  away two levels to stay even with my regular group this way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#A62A