e experience, merely because he had that much more total experience accrued (especially when taking into account the troll and SK penalties). Now, after the experience division change, said SK will take 50/90 of the experience or 56 percent, meaning that the 40th person's experience was increased from 20 percent to 44 percent by that change.<br><br>Using the broadest level range possible, a 40th and a 60th grouped,. prior to the change the 60th would have taken an UNGODLY high percentage of the experience, because it just takes a whole buttload of experience to get to 60. (Experience needed is based on level cubed, and as the levels increase, the curve escalates quickly, so a 60th doesn't need merely 50 percent more experience than the 40th, but more than 300 percent as much.) Now the 60th would take merely 60 percent of the experience, but you KNOW that the 40th person won't be contributing 40 percent of the damage/power in this scenario. In fact, for the 60th to even GET experience, they will need to be fighting mobs that are deep red to the 40th, who will therefore be contributing very little at all, unless he is a cleric or possibly an enchanter.<br><br>The best example of this I have seen in practice was me playing a 47 cleric grouped with four 59-60 folks at Verix in KC. I went all the way through 47 in two hours flat. Of course, the other folks' experience barely moved, but they were glad to have me for the CH ability on the warrior. Two of the people were 50, two were 60, and me. So the xp distribution was this: L60s got 21 percent each, the L59s got 21 percent each (fractionally less than the 60s), and I got 16 percent. The difference was marginal, yet they all needed VASTLY more experience than me, so proportionally I was just gobbling up experience.<br><br>In summary, assuming that whatever you are fighting is worth experience to the highest level person in the group, the lowest level person in the group will gain experience (in terms of bubbles/hour) the quickest, in effect 'catching up'. So whenever possible, it is smart to try to be the lowest level in a group. Obviously that gets harder as you appraoch 60 (as there are simply fewer and fewer people around higher than you). But if you two group together consistently from now on, the lower level person WILL begin to catch up to you. It is in this respect that the change was sneaky: by offloading experience to the lower level people in the group with the linear division change, they made the approach to 60 significantly slower and more difficult, because you HAVE to group with people lower than you as you get closer to 60..<br><br>Anyway, not sure why people keep propogating the myth that the higher levels 'suck xp' in groups when it's been the reverse for quite some time now. So, thought I'd set the record straight on that. It's all pretty basic math here.<br><br>Coriolis of Erudin, Firiona Vie<br>Enchanter of the 51st Circle of Mind Control<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/30/01 10:54:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=753.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balancing Levels</span><hr size=1> woops ... you are correct Antoin.  Forgot about that ...  If that's the case,  here's a couple of other options:<br><br>1.  You might as well just kill the Kerra cats.  They're well-spaced around the zone entrance.  Once you get to level 12, go back to the Warrens ... or #2 below:<br><br>2.  Take the boat toward Qeynos, and then swim toward the island in Erud's Crossing.  The cat people there are on a different faction group ... hopefully friendly to Erudites.  You can hunt kerra spiders, vampire bats, and zombies.  Just pull them toward the shore, and be careful not to pull the spiders in groups.<br><br><br>On a different note:<br><br>Another reminder to those of us who've played for a long time, and a lesson to those who are new to the game:  High and low leveled people can group together to a certain extent -- the guideline for the level differential can be calculated as follows:<br><br>X = lower level character's level<br>Y = higher level character's level<br><br>X * 3 / 2 = Y<br>or<br>Y * 2 / 3 = X<br><br>Which means that a level 10 character can group up with a level 15 character.  A level 16 character *might* be able to group up with a level 10 character.<br><br>If you fulfill the above equation, anything that the higher level character gains experience from will be shared with the lower level.  If a monster is green to the higher level but blue to the lower level, the lower level guy gets experience ... the higher level guy does not (his share is cancelled to zero).<br><br>If you do not fulfill the above equation, the lower level guy will never gain experience while in the party.<br><br><br>The equation is slightly altered when you factor in alignment penalties -- there will be times when the lower leveled members will not gain any experience when they're in a party of opposing alignments.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umheddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mheddik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/30/01 11:05:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=753.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Balancing Levels</span><hr size=1> Let me add one thing: having reread my post there, it sounded like I would turn away someone lower than me to maximize experience, stuff like that. That's not true at all; if someone is fun to be with and we'll both gain experience, I don't really care who is what level. I came to this server to avoid the powergamer mentality, inordinate amounts of twinking, and so on. But I can't help understanding the underlying math and its consequences and effects; it's just in my nature to puzzle out things, particularly mathematical things.<br><br>And in this particular case, explaining how the math works may help these two people stay together, since they will know that the lower level person WILL begin to catch up (assuming they group together consistently). However, the 10th has to get to 11th first to group with the 16th and anyone gain experience. (Lowest level * 1.5 = maximum level for highest)<br><br>My apologies if I gave the impression that I'd let the math dissuade me from grouping with anyone; it doesn't. On the other hand, knowing how it works, I can't say it makes me unhappy when a bunch of folks higher level than me want me along. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Coriolis of Erudin, Firiona Vie<br>Enchanter of the 51st Circle of Mind Control<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 146